===Allocations===
* {{Bgcolortext|up|'''Champion'''}} qualifies for the {{LeagueIconSmall/pubg mobile global championship|date=2025-11-01|}} '''[[PUBG_Mobile_Global_Championship/2025|2025 PUBG Mobile Global Championship - The Gauntlet]]'''
* {{Bgcolortext|stayup|'''Runner-up'''}} qualifies for the {{LeagueIconSmall/pubg mobile global championship|date=2025-11-01|}} '''[[PUBG_Mobile_Global_Championship/2025|2025 PUBG Mobile Global Championship - Group Stage]]'''
{| class="wikitable collapsible collapsed" style="margin:1em 0 0 0"
! Qualification Scenarios&nbsp;
|-
! <small> These scenarios were explained during the BMIC Podcast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://youtu.be/QwGCmulFfvQ|title=BMIC Podcast: Road to Global|publisher='''KRAFTON INDIA ESPORTS'''|date=2025-10-25}}</ref> </small>
|-
|
* If a team that has already qualified for PMGC ([[Orangutan]], [[Dplus]], and [[REJECT]]) finish within the PMGC Group Stage qualifying spot, then:
** The Group Stage slot will be transferred to the next best non-PMGC qualified team.
|-
|
* If [[Orangutan]] are the champions, then:
** The Gauntlet slot will be transferred to the runner up.
** The Group Stage slot will be transferred to the next best team beside [[Dplus]] and [[REJECT]].
|-
|
* If [[Dplus]] qualify for The Gauntlet, then:
** [[DRX]] ([[PUBG_Mobile_Global_Championship/2025/Points/Korea|KR Points]] #2) will inherit their Group Stage slot.
** '''Note:''' [[FN Esports]] ([[PUBG_Mobile_Global_Championship/2025/Points/Korea|KR Points]] #3) will inherit their Group Stage slot instead if [[DRX]] qualify for Group Stage via BMIC results.
|-
|
* If [[REJECT]] qualify for The Gauntlet, then:
** [[REIGNITE]] ([[PUBG_Mobile_Japan_League/Season_5/Phase_2|PMJL]] #2) will inherit their Group Stage slot.
** '''Note:''' [[MAKING THE ROAD]] ([[PUBG_Mobile_Japan_League/Season_5/Phase_2|PMJL]] #3) will inherit their Group Stage slot instead if [[REIGNITE]] qualify for Group Stage via BMIC results.
|}

